    {
      "id": "TwRNpjcbPjFi0dC2FIc-t",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 2298.8835729106054,
      "y": 20645.83286626124,
      "width": 924,
      "height": 250,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bDI",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1209386613,
      "version": 730,
      "versionNonce": 2134424987,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1775614637097,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "why do we need to send iterator to P1, P2 or P3 just for\niterator is iterating to all the user and putting the message in the queue\n(p1, p2, p3) pilling up the queue again consuming by the worker eventually\nto relaise that the message is already sent\n\nSo as part of optimization why do we need to send from Iterator to En-Queue (P1, P2)\nso it better Iterator talk to the Notification tracker database and it check\nif the notification is sent or not and then it goes to the en-queue\n\nNote: For Space optimization we can use Bloom Filters data structure.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "why do we need to send iterator to P1, P2 or P3 just for\niterator is iterating to all the user and putting the message in the queue\n(p1, p2, p3) pilling up the queue again consuming by the worker eventually\nto relaise that the message is already sent\n\nSo as part of optimization why do we need to send from Iterator to En-Queue (P1, P2)\nso it better Iterator talk to the Notification tracker database and it check\nif the notification is sent or not and then it goes to the en-queue\n\nNote: For Space optimization we can use Bloom Filters data structure.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
